		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think you'd have better luck doing something like what Wacky Races does on GBC. I don't want to say it's impossible to do realistic 3D on the NES, but the NES is definitely ill-equipped for it to be practically possible, short of some kind of flashy demoscene-esque demo.

		

